summary: Master’s degree in Geology by the Federal University of Bahia (UFBA)(2016). Bachelor in Oceanography (2013) by the University of Vale do Itajaí (UNIVALI), Santa Catarina, Brazil and Civil Engineering (2020) by  Salvador University (UNIFACS). My research area of expertise is Marine Geology and High Resolution Seismic focused on investigations of Quaternary deposits, coastal engineering, sand deposits, dredging technologies, land reclamation, etc. I have been working on scientific cruises and freelance works for data acquisition and interpretation of geophysics methods (Boomer, Chirp and Sparker). Other research interests are seafloor mapping tools, such as the Multibeam Bathymetry and Side Scan Sonar and seafloor geotechnics
